[Outbreaks of Cryptosporidia in holiday resorts are well known. There can be several sources; especially swimming pools should be suspected here, as it seems that the infection is primarily seen in children. Cryptosporidiosis is frequently reported from swimming pools and water parks (see below). - Mod.EP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3547731,3349.]
